One Move Less?
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to play\b0 .
\par There is a capturing race between Black \'a1\'e3 and White \'a1\'e2.
\par
\par Black has two while White has three liberties. So Black is one move behind.
\par
\par However Black has a nice move to save his stones.
\par }
